Budesonide was excreted in urine and feces in the form of metabolites. After oral as well as intravenous administration of micronized
[ 3H
]-budesonide, approximately 60% of the recovered radioactivity was found in urine. The major metabolites, including 6β-hydroxy budesonide and 16α-hydroxy prednisolone, are mainly renally excreted, intact or in conjugated forms. No unchanged budesonide was detected in urine.
